<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="529" pageId="17" pageNumber="528" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[813,1455,1907,2030]" box="[813,913,1907,1933]" pageId="17" pageNumber="528">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[813,1455,1907,2030]" lastBlockId="18.[132,775,1014,1296]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="529" pageId="17" pageNumber="528">
This species was described under three different names from the same area off Fernandina (Florida); 
<bibRefCitation author="CLENCH W. J. &amp; TURNER R. D." pageId="17" pageNumber="528" pagination="289 - 356" refId="ref22321" refString="CLENCH W. J. &amp; TURNER R. D. 1952. - The genera Epitonium (part 2), Depressiscala, Cylindriscala, Nystiella and Solutiscala in the western Atlantic. Johnsonia 2 (31): 289 - 356. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 41155986" type="journal article" year="1952">Clench &amp; Turner (1952: 337-338)</bibRefCitation>
, acting as First Revisers, selected 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1375,1455,2003,2029]" class="Gastropoda" family="Nystiellidae" genus="Opaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="17" pageNumber="528" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opalina">
<emphasis box="[1375,1455,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="528">opalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the valid name and figured all the 
<typeStatus box="[545,593,1015,1041]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">type</typeStatus>
specimens. Our specimen (
<quantity box="[250,339,1046,1073]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
) is similar in size to the 
<typeStatus box="[598,696,1046,1072]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1927" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1927" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Epitonium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dromia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">Epitonium dromia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DALL W. H." box="[304,427,1078,1104]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref22518" refString="DALL W. H. 1927. - Small shells from dredgings off the southeast coast of the United states by the United States Fisheries Steamer &quot; Albatross &quot;, in 1885 and 1886. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 70 (18): 1 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.70 - 2667.1" type="journal article" year="1927">Dall, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[443,536,1078,1105]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
) but smaller that the 
<typeStatus box="[132,230,1110,1136]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1927" box="[269,403,1110,1136]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Epitonium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opalinum">
<emphasis box="[269,403,1110,1136]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">E. opalinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[420,530,1110,1137]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" unit="mm" value="10.6">10.6 mm</quantity>
). This is the 
<typeStatus box="[674,722,1111,1137]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Clench &amp; Turner, 1952" authorityName="Clench &amp; Turner" authorityYear="1952" box="[207,567,1142,1169]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Nystiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[207,299,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">Nystiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CLENCH W. J. &amp; TURNER R. D." box="[305,567,1142,1169]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" pagination="289 - 356" refId="ref22321" refString="CLENCH W. J. &amp; TURNER R. D. 1952. - The genera Epitonium (part 2), Depressiscala, Cylindriscala, Nystiella and Solutiscala in the western Atlantic. Johnsonia 2 (31): 289 - 356. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 41155986" type="journal article" year="1952">Clench &amp; Turner, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A." pageId="18" pageNumber="529" pagination="297 - 576" refId="ref22019" refString="BOUCHET P. &amp; WAREN A. 1986. - Revision of the Northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitonidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico supplement 2: 297 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén (1986)</bibRefCitation>
treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thiele, 1928" authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1928" class="Gastropoda" family="Nystiellidae" genus="Opaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,775,1174,1200]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">Opaliopsis</emphasis>
Thiele, 1928
</taxonomicName>
. This species was also reported from Brazil by 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDRADE B. G. &amp; COSTA P. M. &amp; SANTOS &amp; PIMENTA A. &amp; DIAS" box="[166,386,1238,1264]" pageId="18" pageNumber="529" pagination="1561 - 1566" refId="ref21638" refString="ANDRADE B. G., COSTA P. M. SANTOS &amp; PIMENTA A. DIAS 2011. - Taxonomic review of the genus Opaliopsis (Gastropoda: Nystiellidae) from Brazil, with description of a new species. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom 91 (7): 1561 - 1566 https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315411000026" type="journal article" year="2011">
Andrade 
<emphasis box="[269,322,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="529">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
. New to Spanish waters and to the eastern Atlantic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
